column8: Drove up the mountain to get stuck in a line of cars to go through a check point for 2 hours. No way of getting out of the line once your in it. Got to the booth and was told it was $56 to go through the check point and I had to hire tire chains at $25 a set. Only two wheel drive cars had to put the chains on. Even though I had a 4x4 I still had to have in my car whether I needed them or not. After 2 and a half hours of being stuck in this line I finally got out and left. Unorganized. Total chaos and a waste of people's time. 👎👎

column8:
Very poorly managed roads, stuck on the road for the whole day without entry to resort on a snowfall day.
Expensive entry during season although listed as a victorian national park.
Lack of enough facilities up the hill to handle large crowds.
Very little on offer to enjoy with the snow.
Good for a day trip and just for a play in the snow.

column8:
Tourists beware this resort/park if it is customer service you seek then visit another snowfield.  This one definately needs some improvement.

My family visited this park on the 9th August 2018 and what a shambles.
We arrived at 10am to be greeted with a huge line of traffic and then took over 3 hours waiting in the car to actually get to the ticket desk with no staff to explain why this was happening..On reaching the ticket desk was told that I had to purchase chains and then pay $20 to have them fitted if I could not do it myself.  I paid the chain hire $20 and the $20 for fitting plus $56 for entry.  After waiting for another half an hour was given a set of chains and told to follow the road where someone would meet us and put the chains on.  Finally saw someone in the middle of the road who said dont need chains you are at the top.  We missed our tour and the kids only had half an hour to play on the toboggan run.  On returning home I contacted guest services (15 August) about a refund for the chain fitting and they told me to fill in a form which I did immediately and  sent back.  As of today 10th September nothing more from them.  This snowfield does not even rate one star......just go somewhere else..

At the first gate, you get charged $28 per person or $56 per car. Then just after the gate they tell you, you have to have chains to continue and they're $20 each. Not sure how much it is to go on the chair lifts but theres probably some nice views up there, we got one good pic from the lower part and the keep dingos there, they were well behaved.

column8:
great place to learn to snowboard and ski or take children.
wouldnt recommend if youre good at snowsports as the mountain runs are short lived.
also a great place to just hang out.
the drive up is horrific though... roads are almost only big enough for one car and busses come flying around the corners and almost put you off the cliffs so always be cautious when driving.

column8: Beautiful place which is about 1500m in elevation. Mount Baw Baw is a mountain on the Baw Baw Plateau and Great Dividing Range, located in Victoria, Australia. The mountain peak falls within the boundaries of the Mount Baw Baw Alpine Resort, which is an unincorporated area of Victoria separate from the Shire of Baw Baw.

After reaching there you need to get entry pass and chain for you car which is 57$ and we went in August 1st week it was drizzling but no snow fall :( but there was lot of snow.

column8:
We had a great stay at Mount Baw Baw. The drive up the mountain is very pretty, and we saw three Lyre Birds which was fun. Parking and village access was very easy. The Toboggan run is a great setup for small kids and with the magic carpet taking you up the hill all day $10 is great value, under 7 is free (when with adult). People were also making snowmen and having snowball fights at the bottom of this section, which was actually hilarious and the kids loved it. We stayed overnight in a lodge which is highly recommended. The Baw Baw staff were super friendly to us, which really made our stay. Highly recommended and we'll be back.

column8:
Mt Bawbaw resort is so money minded and doesn't seem to be fair.
They charge 57$ for entry and they separately charge 10$ again  for playing in the toboggan area. Seriously? 30$ for snow chain again too...
Not everyone can do skiing and if so, the entrance charge you pay is only for looking the mountain only!! If you want to play, another charge on top of it. It feels more like the resort being greedy rather than fair.. Won't recommend for family fun as its boring and not worth the money!!
Choose another place if you want to enjoy snow!
column11:

They charge 57$ for entry and they separately charge 10$ again  for playing in the toboggan area. Seriously? 30$ for snow chain again too...
Not everyone can do skiing and if so, the entrance charge you pay is only for looking the mountain only!! If you want to play, another charge on top of it. It feels more like the resort being greedy rather than fair.. Won't recommend for family fun as its boring and not worth the money!!
Choose another place if you want to enjoy snow!

column8: The snow there is amazing. Among the other snow mountains I would definitely recommend the baw baw mountain. We only found a coffee vending machine and burger barbecue for 10 dollars.

column8:
The resort itself is beautiful and good snow like when I was up, fantstic skiing. Reallly nice staff and great service. The reason for 4 stars is:
- Not many runs
- Some runs where shut even though there was plenty of snow. I went mid August just after the big dump.
- needs chairlifts, after a day hanging onto rope pulls, you really are very sore.
- terrible drive if going from Tanjii Bren. We had to remove 4 fallen large trees on the way up. Lucky we had a tow truck I front of  us to help move them. The other route is much better, but mostly dirt road.
- bit of a walk from car Park to actual ski area.

However , Baw Baw is a really great resort and could be better, if those items listed above where attended to.

column8:
The Staff were all very lovely, but the Food i ordered was not. I ordered Chickpea Curry with Rice... but unfortunately the Rice was mushy.
There just wasn't much fun for my children in terms of activities. We paid for Entry and Tyre Chains to enter, Hired Snow Clothing and Boots, Hired a Toboggan and the kids were hyped up to have a great day.
The Toboggan area was closed for everyone who hadn't purchased a ticket online and there was literally nothing else for 2 young children to do.
We found the whole experience very average, I'm sorry. I wish the experience had been better, but I felt it was a waste of 3hrs driving time each way, and a waste of $400 to do nothing.

We went there this weekend, expecting to ski, while the total skiable area was nothing more than 50 meters!!! So it is not a ski resort, they lie about it! It is only good for very beginner skiers as a very small training area.
The customer service is even more terrible than the low quality service itself.
Don't waste your time and money!

column8:
Went first week of July.
- Small centre that gets crowded during weekends.
- Access in the morning is an issue as many daily visitors haven't done their booking on-line, the resort should manage this better.
- The ski resort charged full lift rate but there was just one lift open which wasn't even going to the end... if I pay for a full roasted chicken I am expecting to have the full roasted rather than just 10%!!
- The worst is the the coffee shop next to the lifts, massive price overcharge for extremely low quality food and nobody cares about the cleaning. Really poor operation.

column8:
First time snowboarding here, regretted in the first 30 mins.

Only 1 lift open and the lift only take up 50 m, have to queue with the learners and get up there faster by walking up.

Definitely not worth coming, if you are looking for good experience skiing/ snowboard. Hotham/Buller is the way.

column8: We visited Baw Baw during the July school holidays. The website is very difficult to navigate considering the requirements to ski here. You can’t hire skis or anything until you collect your lift pass. The building designated as the collection point for pre booked lift passes can only provide passes on the day of the booked pass. The result is long lines every morning to collect ski passes. It would be great if you could print them online. It would also be helpful if you could print off a car pass too. There is way too much to navigate your way through when visiting Baw Baw for the first time.

Mount Baw Baw yields a subpolar oceanic climate (Cfc). The mountain summit receives more annual precipitation than most places in mainland Australia, with frequent and heavy snow in winter (as well as a persistent snowpack). Frequent, heavy cloud-cover and turbulent winds mean that minimum temperatures rarely drop below −5 °C (23 °F), whereas maximum temperatures are frequently at or below 0 °C (32 °F); the mountain is often shrouded in low cloud or mist in winter, thereby reducing diurnal rang

column8:
A wonderful resort,  self contained of grid genaration of its own power, portable water, treatment of waste water and snow making facilities.

1997  saw 3 lp gas power generators fitted    with town lp gas  system to service lodge's with gas for heating  and cooking, gas power generators to enable underground mains power  , removing independent gas bottles and generators.

Plenty of walking tracks that link up to Baw Baw National Park.  Good in the white season winter and green season summer.
On site cafe visiter centre have a grate range of items and grate coffee worth the drive and day trip.

Plenty of accommodation to meet budgets and each lodged have a sense of feel when you enter of many good times over the years.

The sleep is the best, getting up in the morning with peace no noise like the city and enjoy coffee while listening to news and traffic reports on the radio from Melbourne and just put on work shoes and start work.

column11:
A wonderful resort,  self contained of grid genaration of its own power, portable water, treatment of waste water and snow making facilities.

1997  saw 3 lp gas power generators fitted    with town lp gas  system to service lodge's with gas for heating  and cooking, gas power generators to enable underground mains power  , removing independent gas bottles and generators.

Plenty of walking tracks that link up to Baw Baw National Park.  Good in the white season winter and green season summer.
On site cafe visiter centre have a grate range of items and grate coffee worth the drive and day trip.

Plenty of accommodation to meet budgets and each lodged have a sense of feel when you enter of many good times over the years.

The sleep is the best, getting up in the morning with peace no noise like the city and enjoy coffee while listening to news and traffic reports on the radio from Melbourne and just put on work shoes and start work.

column8:
Very disappointed about the facilities offered. They charge $60 entry fee per car which I hoped would be justified by the facilities available inside. But unfortunately it ended up being just a rip off.

The parking area was chaotic and ice/snow had not really been removed properly.

The public toilets were in horrible condition, smelling so bad as soon as you enter. No hot water, no hand dryers or tissue to wipe your hands after washing with freezing cold water. No mirror. Not much thought seemed to be given about visitor health and safety.

The place for Tobbogan rides had only a slight slope and a lot of riders could not slide all the way down. The worst part was that you had to pay another $10 per person if you wanted to go tobboganing. They say its for using the escalator to reach the top which is totally unnecessary.

The two or three restaurants inside the resort were packed around lunch time and seating indoors were ridiculously limited. After waiting in line for about 30-45 min outside in the snow we managed to get in to one and was told it was another 45 min wait for food. So we decided to order just coffe and after 45 min we got a beverage vaguely resembling coffee but not really.

Since we had already realised by that time that there was nothing much to do we decided to just leave the place.

Please avoid going there if you can. It's totally not worth the trouble driving all the way there in winter through the winding roads.

column8:
We paid 99 dollars to enter mount Baw Baw and for chains you didn’t even need to use but you must have them in your car 😡.
Only one cafe/ restaurant was open which down know much about customer service. We had one meal waiting for another which never came until we asked about it.
Now they have put a machine which elevates you to the top instead of walking the hill to do Tabbogani.  I was very disappointed as we spent already 60 dollars to enter and wanted ten dollars each for to adults 😡😡😡😡😡😡
The area was not full of snow that you could even slide down to the end you stop half way because there was grass.
Better to go to another ski resort which has more facilities and better value for money.

column8:
This place is beautiful however hugely disappointed in being charged $54 for entry for a day. Especially with little kids , you can’t even stay all day long as they need to nap during the day!

On top of that 2 out of 4 toilets in the female restrooms did not have toilet paper ! There was a line of women waiting to use only 2 toilets. And when washing your hands there was no paper towel to dry your hands with before heading back out to the freezing snow.

column8:
Went yesterday and there are some positives and negatives.

Positives for me are the extremely helpful staff at the Mount baw baw ski lodge who helped us to put on the ski shoes for us and directed us where to leave our shoes as an extra touch, and the ppl who were patiently directing us to the resort while we were trying to park. The snow views around the resort were amazing!

Negatives for me are the disappointing customer service at the visitor centre who could not produce maps of the village that we want to explore or at least guide us to where the restaurant is. But I want to particularly call out the very appalling customer service at the ski lifts who berated me in front of everyone (and similarly at my friend who was a first timer). It is very unprofessional for a ski operator to lose the temper in front of the customers.

My final comment is the waiting time to get into resort for us was 1hr 30 mins despite having the entry pass pre booked. This was because we were informed the carparks were full and we needed to wait for ppl to leave before entering. Considering that I have seen cars dropping out and "giving up", might be worth thinking how to better manage the traffic into the resort next time.

Overall an ok experience. Could be better.

I was pleasantly surprised snowboarding here having only been to Bulla. The snow was thick, lifts were open (my only comment is I wish they were chair lifts instead) and staff were very helpful! The process of hiring a board and boots was easy - a bit busy but expected for a Saturday in snow season! Get in early as the car park fills up pretty quickly. There are a few restaurants that serve delicious food and beer etc. i would come back for sure!

column11: I was pleasantly surprised snowboarding here having only been to Bulla. The snow was thick, lifts were open (my only comment is I wish they were chair lifts instead) and staff were very helpful! The process of hiring a board and boots was easy - a bit busy but expected for a Saturday in snow season! Get in early as the car park fills up pretty quickly. There are a few restaurants that serve delicious food and beer etc. i would come back for sure!

column8:
The worst thing in this place is they didn’t remove the snow and ice on the pedestrian path through the parking to the whole ski area. Also the kids playing area is way hard to get down, as it’s a very slippery slope which covered with full of ice. So you have to pretty much slide down with sitting position or fall down like ten times to get to the play area.
I don’t understand why the staffs do not try to remove the ice and snow. It looks like they do not care customers safety at all.
It’s my son’s first snow experience and he did NOT enjoy it at all.
I would not recommend anyone to go there.

column8:
We went to ski at Mount Baw Baw from Jun.28 to Jul.03. I bought group lessons and lift pass for 2 kids who are my friend's kids. Later I found this 2 kids were both under 7 years old at that time and according to the terms they should be free of charge which is $520 in total.
I wrote mail to guest service,pushed several times and even provided birth cert finally I was told that they can only give us coupons i/o refund us. This is unacceptable since we didn't cause any loss, this is just lift pass and the the truth is we dont need to pay for that. We dont want to hold the coupon to use after a whole year! And another thing happened also made us very unhappy and dont want to come back.
We ordered 3 day weekend program from Jul.01 to Jul.03, I especially paid attention to the lesson time which was in the morning from 9:00am to 12:00am since we need check out that day right after the lesson. But when we went to the ski course we were told the lesson was to be held in 1 pm! I checked on the website the exact lesson time just disappeared! Also the tickets didn't show any exact time on it that's really tricky. I checked with another person who booked this lesson and she told me she also saw 2 sessions with exact time. And they just denied there were 2 sessioins per day. After talked back and forth they adjusted the lesson on last day to the morning, but it still wasted a lot of time and the process was not very happy.
Now they didn't reply my email at all.

column8:
Enjoyed 4 days with my husband, my mother, and our 6 year old. Great value for children and seniors with free lift tickets and discount parking. Nice easy area for beginners to learn and fun tobogganing.
We stayed in the Altitude Apartments which was very comfortable and close to everything, however it would have been good to know that there were 40 stairs as I would have brought backpacks instead of suitcases.

column8:
A very great place for skiing, or do other activities such as tobogganing. There are dedicated places for tobogganing with escalator where you can enjoy your time in the resort. Distance and drive wise, it’s not too far from Melbourne and you can do a day trip if not lucky enough to find a place to stay. Gears can be hired in cheaper prices in the close by towns. Parking wise, you’ll find good spot if you arrive there early but will need a bit further down the entrance if you get late.

Absolutely beautiful, first snow for me but hubby's been a couple of times to various places around aus and he said it's the best snow he's ever seen. We went a week before school holidays and managed to arrive on one of the best snow days of year. Since we were there before holidays we were one of 6 families and the snow was pristine. Snow upto your knees! Heaps of help from great staff and nooo lines!! Kids loved it and with an autistic child this was perfect. Mt bawbaw is so underrated. We stayed in Erika because we thought the village might be hectic but it was super quiet. We ordered our chains from erika which was a good idea as it gets a bit icy on your way up.

column8:
I recently visited this resort with my family and I must say, I am utterly disappointed with the experience we had. The resort's website advertised a full-day resort pass and toboggan passes for kids, which we eagerly purchased online in advance. However, upon arriving at the resort, we discovered a deceitful policy regarding the toboggan passes that ruined our entire day.

To our shock, we found out that the toboggan passes were only valid for the morning hours, rendering them practically useless for us. This information was conveniently hidden in the fine print, which we missed while making the purchase. As a result, our children were left heartbroken and unable to access the designated play area during our visit.

This misleading practice is absolutely unacceptable. As customers, we relied on the information provided by the resort's website, expecting transparency and fairness. Instead, we were met with a blatant disregard for our time and money. It is disheartening to see a business resort to such deceptive tactics to lure customers in.

Furthermore, the resort's staff did not offer any solutions or alternatives to rectify the situation. Their lack of empathy and willingness to accommodate disappointed guests was truly disappointing. We were left feeling ignored and undervalued as paying customers.

It is vital for businesses to uphold their promises and ensure that the services they offer align with the expectations they set. Unfortunately, this resort failed to deliver on both fronts.

column8:
Went during school holidays but on a weekday. Got lucky to have some snow, and was not crowded. We reached around 11am and stayed till 3 (just sight seeing and toboggan activity).

Highly recommend pre booking resort entry, as it can save you few bucks. Entry to toboggan park can also be pre booked. But around 12:40 the colour of pass changes that means, if you had bought pass in the morning, then you have to pay again $12pp to get another pass for afternoon toboggan park entry. We had no issues with parking spots. Staff friendly and happy to help. Chain fitting can be down for $15 (don’t have to pay to take off chains downhill as long as you have the docket).

Did not ski, so no data to share.

Food and hot beverages options available uphill. But not cheap. Toilet facility available in the restaurants. Found it’s cheaper to rent toboggan downhill from local shops. Highly recommend for parents with school going kids.

Despite the crowds, we still had a fantastic time on the slopes and would recommend Mount Baw Baw for a snow trip, with the caveat to be prepared for the potential for crowds.

column8:
It is 3 hour drive from Melbourne City. Nice place for people, especially kids  to see and enjoy the snow.
No pets allowed!
They charge $60 per car and $33 for (snow) wheel chain. You can hire snow gears at the baw baw village!
Check the weather, snow falls at baw baw before plan your trip! Sometimes less snow in baw baw village may disappoint you!
Plan ahead and go early! If you could, prepare and take your own lunch! There is only one cafeteria and ordinary foods like sandwiches will cost your fortune 😉.

column8:
Today I and my family visited there and they asked to use snow chains for my 4WD car. I told them that this is a 4WD car and don't need chains. But they said that we should use chain and can hire chain service from them. Then i had to pay $39 for chain and chain fitting service from them. Then i had to wait on a queue for more than 1 hour to get chain fit by them. Finally they said that don't need to fit the chain on my car because it is 4WD car but i have to keep the chain on car without fitting for later use if needed. This is funny answer from them, what i realised is that their intention is to earn money by hiring the chains and fitting service.
Other horrible experience is that the people working on fitting and arranging chains are really snails like people 🐌 . They are very lazy guys and wasting visitor's time.. i just want to mention that there was a Chinese looking guy who was hard working while others were chatting and moving around like 🐌 snails..
<The day i visited is 8th July 2023 around 2pm if management want details...>
VERY BAD MANAGEMENT.. HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE.. ☹️☹️☹️☹️ I WILL NEVER GO THERE AND I WILL DEFINITELY MAKE A COMPLAINT ABOUT THIS CHAIN SCAMS TO CONSUMER AFFAIRS..

column8:
I want strict action ageist Jonathan one of the staff member. Very very very rude behaviour from him.
Date 22nd July, We were three family almost 12 people including kids age between 3-10. We were playing near lift area making snowman with kids. One of the staff came and said this area is closed now so we requested him to allow us at least 2 -3 minuets so that we can take some pictures of snowman with kids.
He did not listen and kicked off the snowman Infront of our kids. Kids started crying seeing their beautiful snowman braking down so we told him not to behave such a way because the impression kids were getting. We complained about him but not sure any action has yet taken against him.
The other staff members were nice and listening so thank you to them.

column8:
Horrible experience

I came to Mt Baw Baw expecting snow but the whole point of getting there was gone, there was no snow and all the snow that was there was artificially made.

The lodges was a travesty, there were rats in the walls and the heating wasn't working most of the time.

If anyone is planning to come here including school groups
I recommend not!

column8:
We went there on 5th aug. If you want to see snow, rather pick up another place. We did a whole circuit hike from baw baw village taking the summit trail and back from Mattheus track. The views, vegetation was amazing, we did see a fair bit of snow and that was fun. There was a bollywood event on the day which was a lot of unnecessary loud music. Tobbogan rides slots were booked out, the artificial snow was not as good either. Only recommend if you want to do a whole hike.

column8:
Really bad experience for the kids! Problem wasn’t there was no snow. We found the only place on the mountain in a corner on the toboggan park where we can build a snow man with the kids, it was tuck in a corner so we weren’t distracting or endangering anyone, but was told to leave by the patrols due to safety. And the man in patrols stepped on our  snow man that we build right in front of our kids and toddlers!! Is that really necessary? we were leaving already!
We understand it isn’t anyone’s fault there is no snow this year. But managements can do better than that surely. We paid over $2000 for a dirty old apartment for the weekend up there, found the only fun moment with the kids but got told to leave and people acting so impersonal in front of the kids.
Don’t come to this mountain if you are thinking atleast we can build a snow man because you can’t!
Don’t think we will come back to this mountain again.

column8: Absolute waste of time. Their website showed live snow cam with snow, but when we got there, only artificial snow in ski. No real snow anywhere. They never picked up the phone when we called prior to arrival to check if there have been snow, but no one bothered to answer the phone because they knew if they answered the phone no one would bother turning up. It was overcrowded and looked every bit like a touristy gimmick than a relaxing weekend gateway. There were hundreds of very deeply disappointed visitors today, I overheard so many people venting out who were grossly scammed out because the resort was not honest about lack of snow fall. Toilets are filthy, the restaurant didn’t have enough space and it was not equipped to host that many people. Bottomline is, save your money and time and visit somewhere else which is better equipped and provides honest genuine information prior visitation to avoid major disappointments.

column8:
Nestled in the heart of Victoria's picturesque alpine region, Mount Baw Baw emerges as a quintessential winter wonderland for skiing enthusiasts. During my recent visit, the mountain dazzled under a fresh blanket of snowfall, transforming the landscape into a serene and thrilling playground.

The ski resort offers a variety of slopes catering to all skill levels, making it ideal for both beginners and seasoned skiers alike. For those seeking a challenge, the Summit area provides exhilarating runs with breathtaking views of the surrounding snow-capped peaks. The well-maintained trails ensure a smooth and enjoyable descent, while snowboarders can revel in the terrain parks designed to test their skills with jumps and rails.

Beyond skiing, Mount Baw Baw boasts a cozy village atmosphere with charming lodges and cafes offering warm beverages and hearty meals. The friendly locals and staff contribute to a welcoming ambiance that enhances the overall experience.

One of the highlights of my trip was skiing down the Tank Hill area, known for its gentle slopes and stunning vistas. The combination of crisp mountain air, pristine snow, and thrilling descents made every run memorable.

In conclusion, Mount Baw Baw exceeded my expectations as a winter destination. Whether you're a beginner or an expert, this mountain offers something magical for everyone, ensuring an unforgettable skiing adventure in Australia's beautiful high country.

column11:
Nestled in the heart of Victoria's picturesque alpine region, Mount Baw Baw emerges as a quintessential winter wonderland for skiing enthusiasts. During my recent visit, the mountain dazzled under a fresh blanket of snowfall, transforming the landscape into a serene and thrilling playground.

The ski resort offers a variety of slopes catering to all skill levels, making it ideal for both beginners and seasoned skiers alike. For those seeking a challenge, the Summit area provides exhilarating runs with breathtaking views of the surrounding snow-capped peaks. The well-maintained trails ensure a smooth and enjoyable descent, while snowboarders can revel in the terrain parks designed to test their skills with jumps and rails.

Beyond skiing, Mount Baw Baw boasts a cozy village atmosphere with charming lodges and cafes offering warm beverages and hearty meals. The friendly locals and staff contribute to a welcoming ambiance that enhances the overall experience.

One of the highlights of my trip was skiing down the Tank Hill area, known for its gentle slopes and stunning vistas. The combination of crisp mountain air, pristine snow, and thrilling descents made every run memorable.

In conclusion, Mount Baw Baw exceeded my expectations as a winter destination. Whether you're a beginner or an expert, this mountain offers something magical for everyone, ensuring an unforgettable skiing adventure in Australia's beautiful high country.

column8:
We went just after a massive snow storm so the place looked beautiful.  However, we were sat queuing to get in for just over an hour.  And even though we had brought snow chains with us, couldn't bypass the queue for snowchain hire.   The cafe's are far too small when busy.   The toboggan run is extra money and not that great.

Having done Hotham, Buller and Falls Creek before, I'd put this bottom of the list.   The queue alone and poor organisation at the entry gate is enough to put me off going again.

Plus, someone stole our toboggans from outside the Cafe as have to leave out the front (This didn't change my score though.  Was just annoying)

Sadly to share that my daughter, a friend and I have a poor experience when coming to your mountain which we wanted to do snowboarding so much.

We spent so much money on paying onljne for the parking and the ski lift. Unfortunately, we arrived at your gate around 10:00am and waited for over 3 hours in a very long queue. We were allowed to enter the gate around 1:00pm.

Because of we planned a day trip and have yo return all ski gears to Eureka before 7pm. Due to may be another long queue during leaving the mountain plus we need time pit on the snow chain, we gave up and left the your premises around 2:00pm.

We all decided not coming to Mt. Baw Baw again when we previously have great experience with another ski resorts in Victoria.

column8:
NEVER BOOK TICKETS ONLINE, NO REFUNDS. We made the mistake and were refused a refund on our arrival to the mountain, only a single, short intermediate run was available and a single ski lift for everyone to share. Everything else was closed. I told the staff that a blue run was not suitable for first time skiers, they told me I could purchase extra tickets to use the Toboggins instead, see below for photos of the Toboggin area... The easier section of the blue run was about 25m long, but the line went up up hill for 17m, leaving only 7 meters to ski on a gentle slope before getting to the line. There were about 30 people doing ski lessons, which meant they went to the front of the line each time. While waiting in line, I remember seeing the same instructor and girl get on the lift, come down the slope and re-enter the line 3 times while we waited. Lunch time was slightly less busy, I quenched my thirst with a small can of Redbull for $8. Also on arrival to the car park the driver that was behind be pulled in front of my car, almost attempted to pull into the spot next to me, I shut my door and waved him in so he can park, the poorly shaven and angry looking man says out his window "I work here, Do you have a pass!?" "Do you have snow chains?" He left us alone after I showed him our invoice/chains and he had no reason to ask us to leave (there was no snow or need for chains). Maybe Baw Baw employees should not be hassling customers in the carpark and instead wear a uniform, smile and say "Good morning, welcome to Mount Baw Baw the information desk is just over there" The staff at the ski hire shop were great on the other hand, must be different owners.

column11: NEVER BOOK TICKETS ONLINE, NO REFUNDS. We made the mistake and were refused a refund on our arrival to the mountain, only a single, short intermediate run was available and a single ski lift for everyone to share. Everything else was closed. I told the staff that a blue run was not suitable for first time skiers, they told me I could purchase extra tickets to use the Toboggins instead, see below for photos of the Toboggin area... The easier section of the blue run was about 25m long, but the line went up up hill for 17m, leaving only 7 meters to ski on a gentle slope before getting to the line. There were about 30 people doing ski lessons, which meant they went to the front of the line each time. While waiting in line, I remember seeing the same instructor and girl get on the lift, come down the slope and re-enter the line 3 times while we waited. Lunch time was slightly less busy, I quenched my thirst with a small can of Redbull for $8. Also on arrival to the car park the driver that was behind be pulled in front of my car, almost attempted to pull into the spot next to me, I shut my door and waved him in so he can park, the poorly shaven and angry looking man says out his window "I work here, Do you have a pass!?" "Do you have snow chains?" He left us alone after I showed him our invoice/chains and he had no reason to ask us to leave (there was no snow or need for chains). Maybe Baw Baw employees should not be hassling customers in the carpark and instead wear a uniform, smile and say "Good morning, welcome to Mount Baw Baw the information desk is just over there" The staff at the ski hire shop were great on the other hand, must be different owners.

Still, it’s a fun and accessible option for a day trip or a first-time snow experience.

column8:
The worst experice ever. 2 hour drive to drive there arrived around 12pm to mount baw baw. The maps was showing there a 16 minute delay to get inside (before the pay station) after all that wait there was a guy in vest one of the rangers telling every single individual car one at a time that if they have a reservation they can come in if they don't they can't, and then we where redirected to leave. We asked the ranger what was going on and they said at the top they where at full capacity. So we went and parked on the side of the road and luckily one guy said there is buses we can take to go to the top for free. So we were like nice there is a chance we can still go. The car was parked like 5mins away to where the ranger was and he was like the main big bus broke down and they can't bring people up. We went to the pay booth to see what's happening and the lady was like they're not accepting any more on the spot tickets they're only accepting pre- booked. There was a mini van taking people up and down but it was like a 2 hour wait, the mini van was fit for like 12 people. A waste of day! Anyone going make sure pre book and go early!!! Or else you'll be there a long time.

Moving on, TIRE CHAINS, I waiting for 1 hour getting tire chains at Noojee Bush Goods payed $30 for just the chains. When we went to the mount baw baw they sold chains for $40 (without fitting), $50 with fitting. It's best to just spend the extra $10 rather than wasting an hour.

It's best to plan before you go!!!

column8: I drove up to Mt Baw Baw, and the staff forced me to rent snow chains, insisting that my 4WD couldn’t handle the conditions due to "snow." However, my car was already equipped with mud and snow (M+S) tires, which are more than capable of handling light snow. When I reached the carpark, I saw a 2WD Toyota Corolla driving around freely—proving there was hardly any snow on the road the entire way up. This has happened to many of my friends as well. It’s clear that Mt Baw Baw just wants to charge visitors $49 for unnecessary chain rentals, even when roads are bare and vehicles are fully capable. Shame on them for this dishonest practice!

Mount Baw Baw is a wonderful destination for ski lovers, even though the snow season has ended. While there may not be snow at the moment, the area still offers the charm of the ski slopes, the alpine atmosphere, and beautiful natural surroundings. The mountain is peaceful, with fresh air, scenic trails, and plenty of opportunities to relax and take in the views. It is a great place to enjoy outdoor activities, connect with nature, and imagine the excitement of skiing during the season. The facilities are well maintained, and the staff is always friendly and helpful. Even without snow, visiting Baw Baw is still a rewarding experience, and it makes you want to come back as soon as the snow returns. I highly recommend it for anyone who loves the mountains, winter sports, and spending time in a calm natural environment.

column8:
I recently had the pleasure of visiting Mount Baw Baw for a hiking trip, and it turned out to be one of the most memorable outdoor experiences I’ve had. From the moment we started, the atmosphere was refreshing – the crisp mountain air, the lush greenery, and the peaceful surroundings instantly made the journey feel special. Hiking here is not just about physical activity; it’s about connecting with nature in its purest form. The trails are well-marked and offer something for everyone, whether you’re an experienced hiker or just looking to enjoy a relaxing walk in the mountains. Along the way, we came across stunning viewpoints that offered breathtaking panoramic scenes of the surrounding landscapes. The combination of towering trees, fresh mountain scents, and bird sounds created a sense of calm that is hard to find in busy city life. What truly stood out were the views at different elevations – each stop revealed a new perspective that was even more beautiful than the last. It was the kind of experience that makes you pause, take a deep breath, and truly appreciate nature. The hike wasn’t just exercise; it was uplifting for the mind and soul. Overall, Mount Baw Baw is a destination I would highly recommend to anyone who loves nature, hiking, or simply wants a break from the everyday routine. The experience was incredible from start to finish, and I left feeling refreshed, inspired, and already looking forward to visiting again.
